sections.heading: 45-1,105 to 45-1,107 shall not prohibit a consumer from voluntarily surrendering possession of goods which are collateral and shall not prohibit the creditor from thereafter enforcing any security interest in the goods at any time after default
sections.text: 45-1,105 to 45-1,107 shall not prohibit a consumer from voluntarily surrendering possession of goods which are collateral and shall not prohibit the creditor from thereafter enforcing any security interest in the goods at any time after default.
